{
  "stem": "19690.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "So my mother went back to Speyer alone.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "I stayed with my grandmother, my aunt, and my cousin and we-- she made sure that everything was back in order.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And then my mother-- my grandmother and I went by train, went back home.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "Meanwhile, we got letters regularly from my father, who asked for money so that he could buy things at Dachau.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was at Dachau.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So was my other uncle.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we started sending doctor's reports in indicating that he had a heart condition.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in early December, the 12th of December, all of a sudden one morning, early-- [PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] --the doorbell rang-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] --and this scrawny, bearded man came in.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was my father.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He hadn't had a haircut, he hadn't shaved, he hadn't showered probably in weeks.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He was so emaciated it was unbelievable, but he was home.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My Uncle Ernst did not get released until late in December, just before Christmas.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And when he came home, he was in such horrible mental condition.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He would scream at night, he wet the bed, all the after effects of the internment.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They would tell us that for sometimes they would stand five, six hours in snow and rain out at attention because one of the prisoners was missing and if anybody fell over, they would just leave them lying there.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And a lot of people didn't make it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But this was the gentle Dachau of the early days.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It got worse afterwards.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My Aunt Ruth and my cousin in Italy came home just before my uncle came home in December.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And because they had been in an apartment near the railroad station, they moved in with us because it was safer.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And so they were there when he came home.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
